kdl.prox.qgraph2.tfm
Class TFM21

java.lang.Object
  kdl.prox.qgraph2.tfm.Transformation
      kdl.prox.qgraph2.tfm.TFM21

public class TFM21
extends Transformation

Name: "21. process constraint on an annotated ivertex"

Group: "constraints"

Applicability: Applies to an asterisked, unannotated consolidated vertex that contains all the items in a constraint in the list of constraints for the query.

Behavior: Applies the constraint to the vertex, and removes the constraint from the list

TFMApp usage: Contains one item: {the vertex} (see above).

TFMExec usage: Contains one item copy: {the consolidated vertex} (see above).

NB: Assumes that the vertex with the annotation is NOT connected to more than one vertex. This is because we remove Bs but not the elements that depend on them This works for now, because TFM08 is not implemented

todo : change isApplicable so that this doesn't apply to the case of a B connected to other vertices, when we implement TFM08

execTFMExecInternal

protected java.util.List execTFMExecInternal(QGUtil qgUtil,
                                             NST objTempSGINST,
                                             NST linkTempSGINST,
                                             QGConstraint qgConstraint,
                                             boolean isVertices,
                                             java.lang.String[] edgesOnAnnotatedVertex)
Internal execute method, for the tests. The procedure is: 1. Get the objects from the SGI table for A 2. Get the objects from the SGI table for B 3. If the constraint involves attributes, join the tables above with the corresponding attr vals 4. Create two NSTs that have head/a_item_id , head/b_item_id (or a_attr_value) 5. Call [>=] on those two NSTs, to get the list of rows that will stay 6. Apply the annotation 7. Copy remaining subgraphs and elements into the new SGI tables

It assumes that B is not connected to other vertices that depend on it. This is either because: a. TFM08 is not implemented and therefore B, an annotated item, can not be connected to another
